This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the challenging task of person re-identification, which is a common problem in computer vision. The paper also proposes a machine learning method for this task, which involves learning a distance metric, making it likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as well. The use of privileged information is a relatively new concept in machine learning, which could place this paper in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also involves optimization and decision-making, which could place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with security and privacy concerns related to person re-identification, which could place it in the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
